lops des Euripides ist das einzige vollständig erhaltene Exemplar dieser dramatischen Gattung. Das Stück behandelt die jedem Zuschauer aus der Odyssee wohlbekannte Begegnung des Odysseus mit dem Kyklopen Polyphem.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aCyclopes (Greek mythology)vDrama. 4aEuripides. 4aSatyrspiel. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aEuripides.  asatyr play.1 aSeidensticker, Bernd, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020z9783110704631oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311045338640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311045738440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110457384423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110457384/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020